Motoring website Cars.co.za has announced the winners of its 2018/19 consumer awards. The awards are based on a combination of votes from the public and South African motoring journalists, with a team of judges ultimately determining the final category winners. Eighteen brands were represented in the list of finalists, with Volkswagen leading the nominations with 7 derivatives, followed by BMW and Ford (4 apiece), and Audi, Mercedes-Benz and Volvo (3 apiece). Significantly, Porsche and Isuzu made their first appearances in the final stage of the #CarsAwards programme, while Honda and Range Rover returned to the list of 39 after failing to make the last round in 2017/18. You can find the complete list of winners detailed below. Best Budget Car (under R200,000) Winner: Suzuki Swift 1.2 GL  Compact Hatch (R200,000 – R300,000) Winner: Volkswagen Polo 1.0TSI Comfortline Auto  Adventure SUV (R550,000 – R700,000) Winner: Toyota Fortuner 2.8 GD-6 4×4 Auto  Compact Family (R300,000 – R400,000) Winner: Nissan Qashqai 1.2 Acenta Auto  Family Car (R400,000 – R500,000) Winner: Volkswagen Tiguan Allspace 1.4 TSI Trendline  Leisure Double Cab (R500,000 – R800,000) Winner: Volkswagen Amarok 3.0 V6 TDI 4Motion Highline Plus  Business Class (R600,000 – R800,000) Winner: Volkswagen Arteon 2.0TSI 4Motion R-Line   Executive SUV (R700,000 – R900,000) Winner: Volvo XC60 D5 AWD R-Design  Premium Compact (R450,000 – R600,000) Winner: Mercedes-Benz A200 AMG-Line  Hot Hatch (under R700,000) Winner: Honda Civic Type R  Premium SUV (R1 million – R1.3 million) Winner: Range Rover Velar D300 R-Dynamic SE  Executive Sedan (R800,000 – R1 million) Winner: Mercedes-Benz E220d Avantgarde  Read: How to determine the value of your car